oc:kn_1c31d185 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When calculating WACC" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not use book values for capital structure in WACC calculations. Always use market values for equity weight." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Market values reflect current investor expectations and the true opportunity cost of capital" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_3e0503cb a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SideEffect ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating Excel deliverables" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Valuation tabs are added to the existing Task 2 financial model Excel file, NOT a separate file. Tabs: DCF, Sensitivity, Comps, Precedent Transactions, Valuation Summary." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Keeping all quantitative data in one workbook ensures consistency and traceability across the workflow" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_431efcaf a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RollbackProcedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When prerequisite verification fails" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If Task 2 is not complete, stop Task 3 immediately. Do not attempt placeholder valuations. Inform user that Task 2 must be completed first." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Placeholder valuations create misleading outputs that may be mistaken for complete analysis" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_4ae455f9 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When calculating terminal value in DCF" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Terminal value must represent less than 60-70% of total enterprise value. If it exceeds 70%, the projection period is likely too short." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Excessive terminal value dependence means the valuation is driven by assumptions far into the future rather than near-term projections" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_4b1ad68e a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When reporting valuation results" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never provide a single point estimate for valuation. Always present a range (low/base/high) across scenarios." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Point estimates create false precision and ignore the inherent uncertainty in forward-looking projections" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_5b1b43e9 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When presenting comparable companies analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The comparable companies table MUST include a statistical summary with max, 75th percentile, median, 25th percentile, and minimum for all multiples." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Statistical summary allows readers to quickly assess the distribution and select appropriate multiples" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_66261d9d a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building the valuation framework" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use at least 2 valuation methods: DCF + comparable companies minimum. A single-method valuation is not acceptable for institutional-quality research." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Multiple methods provide triangulation and robustness, reducing reliance on any single set of assumptions" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_7b62c683 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When comparing precedent transaction valuations to trading comps" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Precedent transaction multiples are typically 10-20% higher than trading comps due to control premium and synergies." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Acquirers pay premiums for control rights and synergies that are not reflected in public market trading" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_7e14d56b a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting any valuation work" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do NOT start Task 3 unless Task 2 (Financial Modeling) is complete. Stop immediately and inform the user if the financial model does not exist or is inaccessible." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Starting without a complete financial model results in incomplete valuations and wasted effort" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_947d16a5 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When calculating and validating WACC" ;
    oc:directiveContent "WACC should typically fall in the 8-14% range: 10-14% for tech/high-growth companies, 7-10% for mature/stable companies. Values outside this range require explicit justification." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These ranges reflect typical cost of capital for different risk profiles and serve as a sanity check" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_a751d8b3 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting Task 3" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify Task 2 is complete: financial model exists, file path is known, projected FCF (5 years), revenue projections, EBITDA projections, terminal year metrics, and balance sheet data (debt, cash, shares) are accessible." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Incomplete inputs produce unreliable valuations that cannot be used for investment recommendations" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_b3d62064 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PerformanceProfile ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When estimating output scope" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Output is a 4-6 page markdown valuation analysis document plus 4-5 Excel tabs added to the existing financial model." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_b510fecf a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When reconciling multiple valuation methods into a single price target" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Typical valuation weighting: DCF 40-60%, Trading Comps 25-40%, Precedent Transactions 10-25%. Adjust based on forecast confidence, market conditions, and M&A likelihood." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Weighting reflects the relative reliability and relevance of each method for the specific company" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_eb9400c1 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When setting terminal growth assumptions in DCF" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The perpetuity growth rate should not exceed long-term GDP growth (typically 2.0-3.0%). Use 2.5% as base case." ;
    oc:hasRationale "No company can grow faster than the economy in perpetuity; unrealistic terminal growth distorts intrinsic value" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_ff269164 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After completing valuation analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Run all 7 sanity checks: historical multiple check, peer comparison, implied growth check, market cap reasonableness, terminal value < 70% of EV, WACC in 8-14% range, and implied IRR consistent with recommendation." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Sanity checks catch logical errors and unrealistic assumptions before the analysis is delivered" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

